            <title>[HBASE-9512] Regions can&apos;t get out InRecovery state sometimes when turn off distributeLogReplay and restart a cluster</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9512</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have a test suite where we turn on distributed log replay for one of test case and turn it off for some test cases. Some times when a cluster isn&apos;t clean shut down(there are some RS recovery work left) and cluster restarts, there will be regions in recovery state which is left from previous shut down after the cluster is restarted. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
